&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welsh Student Nurses must apply via the Student Streamlining Process &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exciting opportunity for qualified staff nurses to join our friendly Community hospital. We have 2 wards with a total of 42 beds and an OPD department. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We would welcome motivated nurses who are interested in expanding and moving forward with the services we are able to offer for the future.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are more than happy to coach and Mentor newly qualified Staff Nurses through their Preceptorship&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 16/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tracy Lewis &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Nurse &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tracy.lewis2@wales.nhs.uk &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 03000 850017 &lt;/p&gt;
